---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro"
import Header from "../components/Header.astro"
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro"
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from "../consts"
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title={SITE_TITLE}
      description={SITE_DESCRIPTION}
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Boycott Panda Express!</h1>
      <p>
        Since at least January 1st, 2026, the Panda Express location inside the
        Student Union Building on the University of Utah campus has discontinued
        the <b>Sweetfire Chicken Breast</b>.
      </p>
      <h2>We're Bringing It Back.</h2>
      <p>
        On top of that, they have been gouging prices, skimping on portion
        sizes, and closing earlier than ever before. <i
          >Students are getting shortchanged.</i
        > Gone are the days of picking up a quick plate to get through the night -
        you now have to deal with the poorest selections they have for more money
        and less food.
      </p>
      <h3>Join the boycott!</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <b>Don't buy Panda Express</b> until they bring back Sweetfire Chicken!
        </li>
        <li>Share with your friends!</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>What are my alternatives?</h2>
      <ul id="alternatives">
        <li>
          <h3>Kafe' Mamai</h3>
          <div class="divider"></div>
          <p>
            Delicious African-Caribbean fusion cuisine. This small business
            deploys a food truck during lunch hours, and has an in-person
            location in downtown Salt Lake, at the Gallivan Plaza.
          </p>
          <h4>Recommended Items</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <h5>Jerk Chicken Sandwich</h5>
              <p>
                This sandwich consists of a pita bread wrapping delicious
                jerk-style chicken. It comes with a healthy serving of fries -
                sweet potato and regular - and a signature sauce. You get better
                food, more food, and support small business purchasing here.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            Parked right outside the Union from 10:15 to about 2:00 each day,
            right in time for a delicious lunch.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Jeeva's</h3>
          <div class="divider"></div>
          <p>
            Greek food in the Garff Building, close to South Campus. They have a
            couple of locations - of course, the Garff building, but also the
            City Creek and Fashion Place mall, among others. A familiar favorite
            if you frequent those malls!
          </p>
          <h4>Recommended Items</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <h5>Lamb Gyro</h5>
              <p>
                This Gyro is make with lamb, tomatoes, feta cheese, and their
                signature Tzatziki sauce. You can get just the sandwich or have
                your choice of fries, greek salad, or lemon rice with it.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <h5>Souvlaki Stick(s)</h5>
              <p>
                These kebabs come in singles or doubles, in chicken or beef.
                Delectably seasoned and comes with a pita bread, greek salad,
                and lemon rice. Served with a side Tzatziki sauce.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <h5>Greek Burger</h5>
              <p>
                This classic Greek burger blends a juicy beef patty with their
                signature Tzatziki sauce. If you can't get enough of the Greek
                taste, this burger puts a great twist on a classic.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            This business is open from 10:00 to 5:00 in the Garff building. Open
            almost as late as Panda these days, and a much better option.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h3>Starley Commons</h3>
          <div class="divider"></div>
          <p>
            A quaint little Caf√© located in the upper Warnock. Serves hand-made
            sandwiches, soups, and salads (among other items). Has a panini
            press, coffee machine, microwave, and anything else you'd need to
            make your perfect breakfast.
          </p>
          <h4>Recommended Items</h4>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <h5>Soup</h5>
              <p>
                The variety soups are always a classic warm meal, best for a
                cold day. They come with a bread roll and crackers, too! The
                Perfect Chili is a common one to find, but don't hesitate to try
                out the other soups!
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <h5>Sandwiches</h5>
              <p>
                With a variety of sandwiches, from turkey croissants to pesto
                provolone to reubens, and a panini press to boot, these never
                miss. Also, check out the half and half sandwich/soup combo!
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            This business is open from 9:00 to 2:30 in the Warnock Engineering
            Building, tucked away in a corner of the Catmull Gallery. A great
            option for breakfast and lunch, and without the lengthy walk from
            the engineering side of campus to the Union.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  #alternatives {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  #alternatives ol {
    list-style: reset;
  }

  .divider {
    width: 100%;
    border: 1px solid black;
  }
</style>
